{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":250606,"duration_api_ms":249633,"num_turns":3,"result":"Here's what I found across the ultrainit codebase:\n\n---\n\n### Architecture\n\n**Pipeline Orchestrator Pattern** — Five discrete phases (`gather.sh`, `ask.sh`, `research.sh`, `synthesize.sh`, `validate.sh`/`merge.sh`) each live in their own `lib/` file. `ultrainit.sh:139-176` calls them in sequence. Phases communicate exclusively through files in `.ultrainit/` and share a `state.json` for resumability.\n\n**Agent Runner Abstraction** — Every `claude -p` invocation goes through `run_agent` in `lib/agent.sh:28-163`. No caller invokes Claude directly. The function handles resumability, budget enforcement, system prompt injection, large-prompt stdin piping (>100KB), response envelope validation, and cost recording.\n\n**Two-Pass Synthesis** — `lib/synthesize.sh:21-76` runs two sequential large-context passes. Pass 1 generates CLAUDE.md from raw findings; Pass 2 receives that generated CLAUDE.md as source of truth and produces skills/hooks/subagents. Sequential by design — Pass 2 depends on Pass 1 output.\n\n---\n\n### Error Handling\n\n**Tiered Error Tolerance** — Three failure tiers: critical failures (identity/structure-scout missing, or ≥3 of 8 core agents fail) abort the phase (`gather.sh:85-102`); non-critical failures warn and continue; synthesis failures retry up to `$ULTRAINIT_MAX_RETRIES` with 10s sleep (`synthesize.sh:319-361`). Validation failures trigger an automatic revision agent instead of hard-failing (`validate.sh:115-122`).\n\n**`set -euo pipefail` at script boundaries** — Set at the top of all entry-point scripts and in every generated parallel-agent temp script (`agent.sh:192-195`). Functions use explicit `return 0/1`. Errors go to stderr via `>&2`. Tests intentionally omit this to capture non-zero exits.\n\n**Diagnostic Logging via Claude** — `diagnose_phase_failure` (`agent.sh:244-312`) collects the last 50 lines of each failed agent's stderr, then makes a cheap haiku call (max $0.05) to interpret errors and suggest fixes.\n\n---\n\n### Configuration & State\n\n**Global Exported Variables** — All runtime config lives in exported globals (`SCRIPT_DIR`, `WORK_DIR`, `FORCE`, `AGENT_MODEL`, `TOTAL_BUDGET`, etc.) with defaults set via `${VAR:-default}` in `config.sh:6-16`. CLI args override defaults; `ULTRAINIT_*` env vars are a secondary layer.\n\n**Explicit Variable Propagation to Subprocesses** — Parallel agents re-source `config.sh`, which would clobber computed values. `run_agents_parallel` (`agent.sh:191-211`) bakes current values as literals into each temp script before sourcing libs, with an explicit comment explaining why.\n\n**JSON State File for Phase Tracking** — `$WORK_DIR/state.json` stores `{ \"gather\": \"<ISO timestamp>\", ... }`. `mark_phase_complete` and `is_phase_complete` in `utils.sh:26-49` handle null-safety and corruption recovery.\n\n**Per-Agent Cost Files** — Each agent writes to `$WORK_DIR/costs/{agent}.cost` (`agent.sh:9-16`) to avoid race conditions during parallel execution. Aggregation uses `awk` + `bc` for floating-point arithmetic.\n\n---\n\n### Naming\n\n**snake\\_case with semantic prefixes** — All functions use snake\\_case with consistent prefixes: `log_*`, `run_*`, `is_*`, `mark_*`, `json_*`, `validate_*`, `build_*`, `write_*`, `merge_*`, `check_*`, `compute_*`, `estimate_*`. Applied consistently across all 9 lib files with zero CamelCase.\n\n**kebab-case for agent/artifact names** — All agent names, schema files, and prompt files use kebab-case (`git-forensics.json`, `docs-scanner.md`, `structure-scout.json`). `scripts/validate-skill.sh` enforces kebab-case for generated skill names as a hard validation check.\n\n---\n\n### Testing\n\n**PATH-Based Mock Claude** — A fake `claude` binary is written to a temp dir prepended to `$PATH` (`mock_claude.bash:18-104`). Supports single-response mode, per-agent dispatch mode (keyed by agent name → response file), controlled exit codes, and call logging for assertions.\n\n**Fixture-Based Testing with Envelope Helper** — `tests/fixtures/` holds realistic JSON for all agent types. `make_claude_envelope` (`test_helper.bash:81-89`) wraps structured output into the real `claude -p` response format `{is_error, total_cost_usd, structured_output}`.\n\n**Test Files Map 1:1 to Lib Files** — `tests/unit/config_budget.bats` → `lib/config.sh`, `tests/unit/agent_run.bats` → `lib/agent.sh`, etc. Separate directories for unit, integration, scripts, and edge cases.\n\n---\n\n### Other Consistent Patterns\n\n- **Null-safe jq**: Every optional field uses `// empty`, `// []`, or `// {}` with `2>/dev/null` guards — consistent across all lib files\n- **TTY-aware logging**: Color codes conditionally set via `[[ -t 1 ]]` at source time (`utils.sh:4-14`); spinner only activates in interactive TTYs\n- **Atomic writes**: Writes go through `.tmp` intermediates with `mv` to finalize (`synthesize.sh:400`), `mktemp` for temp dirs with explicit cleanup (`agent.sh:178`)","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"47ebe8aa-25e9-4106-bf7d-073049d2cbce","total_cost_usd":0.5262109,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":42473,"cache_read_input_tokens":65983,"output_tokens":5673,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":42473,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":1393,"cache_read_input_tokens":39042,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3431,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3431},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"inputTokens":7,"outputTokens":5673,"cacheReadInputTokens":65983,"cacheCreationInputTokens":42473,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.26418465,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":107,"outputTokens":13960,"cacheReadInputTokens":989255,"cacheCreationInputTokens":74555,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.26202625,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"patterns":[{"name":"Pipeline Orchestrator Pattern","type":"architecture","evidence_files":["ultrainit.sh","lib/gather.sh","lib/ask.sh","lib/research.sh","lib/synthesize.sh","lib/validate.sh","lib/merge.sh"],"description":"Five discrete phases (Gather → Ask → Research → Synthesize → Validate/Write) each implemented as a single function in its own lib/ file. The main orchestrator (ultrainit.sh lines 139-176) calls each phase function in sequence. Phases are independent, communicate via files in .ultrainit/, and use a shared state.json to mark completion. This enables resumability: each phase guards with `if is_phase_complete \"phase\" && [[ \"$FORCE\" != \"true\" ]]; then return 0; fi` (gather.sh:7, synthesize.sh:16, ask.sh:28).","is_consistent":true},{"name":"Agent Runner Abstraction","type":"architecture","evidence_files":["lib/agent.sh"],"description":"All Claude invocations funnel through a single `run_agent <name> <prompt> <schema_file> <allowed_tools> [model] [phase]` function (agent.sh:28-163). It handles: resumability (skip if findings exist), budget enforcement, system prompt file injection, large-prompt stdin piping (>100KB), response envelope validation, cost recording, and structured output extraction. No caller invokes `claude -p` directly.","is_consistent":true},{"name":"Two-Pass Synthesis","type":"architecture","evidence_files":["lib/synthesize.sh","prompts/synthesizer-docs.md","prompts/synthesizer-tooling.md"],"description":"Synthesis is split into two sequential large-context passes (synthesize.sh:21-76). Pass 1 (Docs) receives all raw findings and produces CLAUDE.md files. Pass 2 (Tooling) receives the generated CLAUDE.md from Pass 1 as its source of truth and produces skills/hooks/subagents. Sequential because Pass 2 depends on Pass 1 output. Findings are filtered per pass via `build_docs_context` and `build_tooling_context` to extract only relevant fields.","is_consistent":true},{"name":"Tiered Error Tolerance","type":"error_handling","evidence_files":["lib/gather.sh","lib/agent.sh","lib/validate.sh","lib/synthesize.sh"],"description":"Three failure tiers: (1) Critical failures (identity or structure-scout agent missing, or ≥3 of 8 core agents failed) abort the phase (gather.sh:85-102). (2) Non-critical failures (individual deep-dive agents, research agents) log a warning and continue. (3) Synthesis failures retry up to `$ULTRAINIT_MAX_RETRIES` times with a 10-second sleep before aborting (synthesize.sh:319-361). Validation failures trigger an automatic revision agent rather than hard failure (validate.sh:115-122).","is_consistent":true},{"name":"set -euo pipefail at Script Boundaries","type":"error_handling","evidence_files":["ultrainit.sh","lib/agent.sh","scripts/validate-skill.sh","scripts/validate-subagent.sh"],"description":"`set -euo pipefail` appears at the top of all top-level scripts (ultrainit.sh:2, scripts/validate-skill.sh, scripts/validate-subagent.sh) and in every generated parallel-agent temp script (agent.sh:192-195). Functions use explicit `return 0/1` and capture exit codes with `local exit_code=$?` (agent.sh:110). Error messages go to stderr via `>&2` (utils.sh:20). Tests intentionally omit this to allow capturing non-zero exits.","is_consistent":true},{"name":"Diagnostic Logging via Claude","type":"error_handling","evidence_files":["lib/agent.sh"],"description":"On phase failure, `diagnose_phase_failure` (agent.sh:244-312) collects the last 50 lines of each failed agent's stderr log file, then makes a low-cost `claude -p` call (haiku, max $0.05) to interpret the errors and suggest fixes. Falls back to printing raw logs if Claude itself is unavailable. Agent stderr is always captured to `$WORK_DIR/logs/{name}.stderr` (agent.sh:77).","is_consistent":true},{"name":"Global Exported Variables as Configuration","type":"configuration","evidence_files":["lib/config.sh","ultrainit.sh","lib/agent.sh"],"description":"All runtime configuration lives in exported global variables: SCRIPT_DIR, TARGET_DIR, WORK_DIR, FORCE, NON_INTERACTIVE, VERBOSE, DRY_RUN, AGENT_MODEL, SYNTH_MODEL, TOTAL_BUDGET, GATHER_BUDGET, AGENT_BUDGET, AGENT_PHASE, etc. Defaults set in config.sh using `${VAR:-default}` syntax (config.sh:6-16). CLI argument parsing in ultrainit.sh (lines 80-98) overrides defaults. Environment variables (ULTRAINIT_MODEL, ULTRAINIT_BUDGET) are a secondary override layer.","is_consistent":true},{"name":"Explicit Variable Propagation to Subprocesses","type":"configuration","evidence_files":["lib/agent.sh"],"description":"Parallel agents run as child bash processes that re-source lib/config.sh, which would clobber computed values. To prevent this, `run_agents_parallel` writes a temp script per agent (agent.sh:191-211) that hard-bakes current variable values as `export VAR=\"$VAR\"` literals before sourcing libs. This is explicitly documented in a comment: 'Propagate parent state explicitly; these literal values are baked in'.","is_consistent":true},{"name":"JSON State File for Phase Tracking","type":"state_management","evidence_files":["lib/utils.sh"],"description":"`$WORK_DIR/state.json` tracks phase completion as `{ \"gather\": \"<ISO timestamp>\", \"synthesize\": \"...\", ... }`. `mark_phase_complete` (utils.sh:26-39) writes atomically with null-safety: re-initializes to `{}` if file is corrupt, validates with `jq empty` before overwriting. `is_phase_complete` (utils.sh:42-49) uses `jq -e` to return a boolean. All phase functions check this before executing.","is_consistent":true},{"name":"Per-Agent Cost Files to Prevent Race Conditions","type":"state_management","evidence_files":["lib/agent.sh","lib/config.sh"],"description":"Each agent writes its cost to its own file: `$WORK_DIR/costs/{agent-name}.cost` (agent.sh:9-16), format: `phase|agent|cost`. Because parallel agents run simultaneously, using a shared file would cause race conditions. `check_budget` (config.sh:88-108) aggregates all `.cost` files via `awk -F'|' '{ sum += $3 }'` and compares against `TOTAL_BUDGET` using `bc` for floating-point arithmetic.","is_consistent":true},{"name":"snake_case Function Naming with Semantic Prefixes","type":"naming","evidence_files":["lib/utils.sh","lib/agent.sh","lib/config.sh","lib/gather.sh","lib/validate.sh"],"description":"All functions use snake_case. Prefixes are semantically consistent across the entire codebase: `log_*` (logging), `run_*` (execution), `is_*` (boolean checks), `mark_*` (state mutation), `json_*` (JSON utilities), `validate_*` (validation), `build_*` (context builders), `write_*` (file I/O), `merge_*` (merging), `check_*` (precondition checks), `compute_*` (calculations), `estimate_*` (estimation), `setup_*` (initialization), `get_*` (retrieval), `diagnose_*` (error analysis), `backup_*` (file backup). No CamelCase anywhere.","is_consistent":true},{"name":"kebab-case for Agent/Artifact Names","type":"naming","evidence_files":["schemas/","prompts/","lib/gather.sh","scripts/validate-skill.sh"],"description":"All agent names, schema files, and prompt files use kebab-case: `git-forensics.json`, `docs-scanner.md`, `structure-scout.json`, `domain-researcher.md`, `mcp-discoverer.md`. The skill validator (validate-skill.sh) enforces kebab-case for skill names as part of its frontmatter checks. This convention also applies to generated artifact filenames.","is_consistent":true},{"name":"BATS Test Framework with PATH-Based Mock","type":"testing","evidence_files":["tests/helpers/test_helper.bash","tests/helpers/mock_claude.bash","tests/unit/agent_run.bats","tests/unit/config_budget.bats","Dockerfile.test"],"description":"Tests use bats-core running inside Docker for isolation (Dockerfile.test). No real Claude calls are made. A mock `claude` binary is written to a temp directory prepended to `$PATH` (mock_claude.bash:18-104). The mock supports three modes: single response (MOCK_CLAUDE_RESPONSE), per-agent dispatch (MOCK_CLAUDE_DISPATCH_DIR maps agent name to response file), and controlled exit codes (MOCK_CLAUDE_EXIT_CODE). All invocations are logged to MOCK_CLAUDE_LOG for assertions.","is_consistent":true},{"name":"Fixture-Based Testing with Envelope Helper","type":"testing","evidence_files":["tests/helpers/test_helper.bash","tests/fixtures/","tests/unit/agent_run.bats"],"description":"Realistic JSON fixtures for all agent types live in `tests/fixtures/findings/` and `tests/fixtures/synthesis/`. The `make_claude_envelope` helper (test_helper.bash:81-89) wraps structured output into the real `claude -p --output-format json` response format: `{is_error, total_cost_usd, structured_output}`. Tests set up responses with `make_claude_envelope '{...}' '0.42' > \"$MOCK_CLAUDE_RESPONSE\"` before calling functions under test.","is_consistent":true},{"name":"Co-located Test File Organization by Layer","type":"testing","evidence_files":["tests/unit/","tests/integration/","tests/scripts/","tests/edge/"],"description":"Tests are organized into separate directories by layer, not by feature: `tests/unit/` (individual functions), `tests/scripts/` (standalone validator scripts), `tests/integration/` (phase-level and full pipeline), `tests/edge/` (budget exhaustion, CLI args). Each unit test file maps 1:1 to a lib/ file (e.g., `config_budget.bats` tests `lib/config.sh` budget functions, `agent_run.bats` tests `run_agent` in `lib/agent.sh`).","is_consistent":true},{"name":"Null-Safe jq Operations Throughout","type":"other","evidence_files":["lib/utils.sh","lib/synthesize.sh","lib/merge.sh","lib/agent.sh"],"description":"Every jq expression that reads optional fields uses `// empty`, `// []`, or `// {}` fallbacks. Examples: `jq -r \"$key // empty\" \"$file\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"\"` (utils.sh:57), `.directories[] | select(.priority == \"high\" or .priority == \"medium\")` with `2>/dev/null` guards (synthesize.sh:125), `.settings_hooks[$i].matcher // empty` (merge.sh:195). This guards against Claude returning partial or missing fields in structured output.","is_consistent":true},{"name":"TTY-Aware Logging with Color Codes","type":"other","evidence_files":["lib/utils.sh"],"description":"Color escape codes are conditionally defined at source time: `if [[ -t 1 ]]; then RED='\\033[0;31m' ...; else RED='' ...; fi` (utils.sh:4-14). This means CI/pipe output is clean text, terminal output is colored. A spinner (`spin` function) only activates in interactive TTYs. Tests explicitly export empty color variables to keep assertion output clean.","is_consistent":true},{"name":"Atomic File Writes via Temp Files","type":"other","evidence_files":["lib/agent.sh","lib/synthesize.sh"],"description":"Writes to important output files go through a `.tmp` intermediate: write to `${output_file}.tmp`, then `mv \"$tmp_file\" \"$output_file\"` (synthesize.sh:400). `mktemp` with a template (e.g., `mktemp -d \"${TMPDIR:-/tmp}/ultrainit-agents.XXXXXX\"`) is used for temp directories (agent.sh:178), with explicit `rm -rf \"$tmp_dir\"` cleanup after use.","is_consistent":true}]},"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"b74c3713-cf4e-436e-8c73-1e0717db88ec"}
